<|startoftext|>I'm not sure if I can give this restaurant a 5 star rating, but I feel like I did a great job this year! After moving out to Arizona from my home in San Jose, I wasn't looking forward to this place opening. I know the restaurant is pretty far to the side of the building, so the kitchen has a lot of space for cooking, but there are very few tables in the restaurant! \n\nThis place gets really crowded when it is busy, so we got our food seated at a table right off the bar. However, the bartenders will bring you your drinks whenever you are within a few feet of the bar. \n\nThe menu has a variety of choices, so you're going to be able to try a lot of different dishes. I tried the spicy tuna wrap, but the avocado served on top of it is what pulled the whole dish out of the blue. The dressing was light, but very delicious. I would have had my heart set on this dish, but it was just too big for me, so my friend had the steak filet with spicy mayo in a crab cake crust. All of our entrees came with the side of potatoes, so they were a little more on the oily side, but the potatoes were light and tender and we all loved them! \n\nThe service was quick and the food came out extremely quickly. I'm happy to say we did not see this place being completely full until close to closing, which was awesome for some people! The only issue with the food was that it took over 10 minutes to put our order, however, we got it all done during dinner! \n\nAll of the chefs on this place are so friendly, and I would recommend going to Eat23 anytime you can for drinks, food, and service!<|endoftext|>
