<|startoftext|>Went to the restaurant on Saturday evening for a late dinner and was promptly greeted and seated by the owner Alex. He offered us to sit a small table and I made my choice.\n\nWhen the tables are full, we are in the middle of a communal table with two other couples. The food is great here, very delicious and very reasonably priced. The menu had a lot of options and was very simple. The food was served with a fork, a plate of rice and a little side salad that was the perfect mix of creamy, light and healthy ingredients that complimented the rice and salad. I ordered the shrimp scampi and my wife ordered the steak salad w thin slices of fresh meat in fresh tomato slices. The scampi was delicious with thick dollops of feta and a little balsamic dressing that complemented perfectly the thick cut crust of the shrimp.\n\nThe restaurant is very intimate and there are table spines, chairs and small round tables inside. The patio is awesome and is nice if the weather is right. The dining area is very clean and I love that you can see all of the cooking and grinding in the kitchen below you.\n\nThere's also a bar and a few smaller areas that you can find with couches overlooking the pool, walkways and outdoor seating.\n\nThe interior is very stylish and inviting. The outside has all white decor which was a nice change from the more subdued décor that most clubs would run in the same color palette. It's the perfect place for a special dinner\/special club\/bachelor party and I definitely recommend it.<|endoftext|>
